********************************************************************************

--- Compile

1. cd convertor
2. javac xbneditor/*.java

--- Run

1. GUI mode as an editor: "java xbneditor/Standalone" as editor 
   --- you can open BBN file, edit it, and save it to .bif, .xml or .net format

2. Command line mode as a convertor: "java xbneditor/BBNConvertor [sourcefilename] [targetfilename]"
   --- you can directly convert BBN file from one format to another format 
 
   For example, to convert alarm from HUGIN .net format to XMLBIF .xml
format:
   java xbneditor/BBNConvertor alarm.net alarm.xml
